quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  11,89,"O my people! Let not a breach with me cause you to so sin that there befall you the like of that which befell the people of Noah, or the people of Hud, or the people of Salih, nor are the people of Lot far off from you"
  11,90,"So ask pardon from your Lord, then turn to Him repentant; verily, my Lord is Merciful, Loving"
  11,91,"They said, \"O Shu´eyb! We do not understand much of what you say, and we see that you are weak (powerless) amongst us; and were it not for your family we would stone you, nor could you have power over us"
  11,92,"He said, \"O my people! Are my family more esteemed by you than Allah? Or have you taken Him as something to cast behind your backs? Verily, my Lord, surrounds all you do"
  11,93,"O my people! Act according to your power; verily, I too will act, and you soon will know on whom comes a doom that will abase them, and him who is a liar. Watch then; verily, I am watching with you"
  11,94,"And when Our commandment came, We saved Shu´eyb, and those who believed with him, by Our Mercy; and the great noise seized those who had done wrong, and on the morrow they were found prostrate in their houses"
  11,95,As though they had not dwelt therein. Behold! Removed was Midian! As was removed Thamud
  11,96,And We sent Moses with our signs (revelations) and with obvious (clear) power
  11,97,"Unto Pharaoh and his chiefs; but they followed the command of Pharaoh, and the command of Pharaoh was no right (or true, straight) guidance"